<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2826] LineDocSource should assign stable IDs; docdate field should be NumericField</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2826</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Some small enhancements when indexing docs from a line doc source:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Assign docid by line number instead of by number-of-docs-indexed;&lt;br/&gt;
    this makes the resulting ID stable when using multiple threads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The docdate field is now indexed as a String (possible created&lt;br/&gt;
    through DateTools).  I added two numeric fields: one that indexes&lt;br/&gt;
    .getTime() (= long msec) and another that indexes seconds since&lt;br/&gt;
    the day started.  This gives us two numeric fields to play&lt;br/&gt;
    with...&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
